&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="suppawow" src="https://aggerdom.github.io/images/suppawow.png"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To include an image file. Use the format:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;![ ALTTEXT ](/images/FILENAME)
&lt;/pre&gt;


&lt;p&gt;To center an image. Use the html center tags.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;center&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; ![suppawow](/images/suppawow.png) &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;/center&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;


&lt;p&gt;To scale the image first, I will probably just be easier to use html, since
I haven't figured out how to use alternative implimentations of markdown with nikola yet (Though mau may be an option.).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;img&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;src&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;"/images/suppawow.png"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;alt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;"ALT TEXT"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;style&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;"width: 200px;"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://aggerdom.github.io/images/suppawow.png" alt="ALT TEXT" style="width: 200px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>learning Nikola</category><guid>https://aggerdom.github.io/blog/test-markdown-post.html</guid><pubDate>Sun, 30 Aug 2015 22:34:36 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>